values: few things in the world compare to a night of cheap beer, leftover chinese and comic books

I really enjoyed it, but I had a few realizations during the movie.

     -More dangerous to society than having violence/sex/swearing in a movie is happy endings. They convince us that our lives will be ok. That despite all the trials and tribulation in the end it will all be worth it. to which I say "Bullshit".

     -Saying you're gonna peel the flesh off of someones bones is a kick-ass threat...especially if it's one you're capable of.
My car was egged tonight....i'm not entirely sure how i feel about that.
I got latex gloves caught in my zipper twice today...occupational hazzard, I guess.
Jason Webley was awesome tonight. He sang a song about my mom, and then asked her how to pronounce the names of various flowers.

OH MY GOD!!!   I just got back from seeing Bubba Ho-Tep (the new Bruce Campbell movie). It fucking rocks. I highly recommend seeing it if you get the chance. It's playing at the Castro until Thurs (if you're in the sf area).  Bruce Campbell plays a geriatric Elvis in a retirement home who teams up with an elderly black man (who's convinced he's JFK), to battle a mummy who sucks out souls through peoples asses. And the best part, the movie actually manages to be touching at moments.  There has never been a better idea for a movie. EVER!!!

Today sucked. Work sucked and it jsut went downhill from there. All in all, the most depressing day I've had in a long time. And I've got to go to work tomorrow morning so now I need to try to go to sleep. heh.

Over-view of the past week:
       -Worked a bunch, which sucked but I need the money
       -Went to a coupla fun shows, which rocked
       -Saw "Once Upon a Time in Mexico". It was a pretty fun movie
       -Played poker with some highschool buddies (won $3 too)
       -etc.....

And now I'm going to bed because I have to get up early to go to the DMV  to renew my licence, because it's been expired since Feb.

Dagnabbit, I thought I was done with this cursed site. 

Shrug. Oh well, wahtever...
